Sentencas: A chemical etching technique was used as a pretreatment of commercially available 8 mol % yittria stabilized zirconia (8YSZ) electrolyte to improve solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) performance.
Titulo: Effect of chemically etched electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell performance

Sentencas: It was found that the etching rate of the 8YSZ increased linearly with increases in hydrofluoric acid (HF) concentrations.
Titulo: Effect of chemically etched electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell performance

Sentencas: Increasing the temperature of both a HF solution and a HF + HCl (hydrochloric acid) solution accelerated the etching rate.
Titulo: Effect of chemically etched electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell performance

Sentencas: Cell performance was improved not only by thinning the electrolyte but also by improved electrode performance, especially for the lanthanum strontium manganite (LSM) + YSZ composite cathode.
Titulo: Effect of chemically etched electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell performance

Sentencas: An electrode kinetics analysis and scanning electron microscope (SEM) results suggest that this improved electrode performance was due to increases in three phase boundary (TPB) area.
Titulo: Effect of chemically etched electrolyte on solid oxide fuel cell performance
